title: Grateful Dead Live at The Omni on 1993-03-21
lineage: Soundfield ST-250's (FOB/DFC) > Sony D10 Pro-II (48k) > DAT clone (1st gen) > Sony PCM-M1 > Edirol UA-5 (hardware resample to 44.1) > USB out > Cooledit 2000 > CD Wave > mkwACT > SHN
description: Feel Like A Stranger, West L.A. Fadeaway, Black Throated Wind, Candyman, Queen Jane Approximately, Brown Eyed Women, Eternity, Liberty Samson & Delilah, Way To Go Home, Broken Arrow, Saint Of Circumstance-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> The Days Between-> Around & Around, E:Baba O'Riley-> E: Tomorrow Never Knows

reviews.review_text: great first set As was usually the case on this tour, first sets were smokers. I was fortunate to catch this 3 night omni run. Jerry brought his A game. Can't get enough of this candyman. Aside from some chatter, this is a very good sounding aud. much thanks to the tapers. peace, Gary

Insanity! I caught all 3 of these shows too !!!!

The encores were just magic!!!!!
Took me to a whole different level.........

Man, i really miss Jerry.
THIS IS A GREAT SHOW!!!
Since no one else has, let me be the first to encourage others that missed this gift from god.
Broken Arrow................Phil your face............
Way to go home.................Waffle cone to the forehead!

Need i Go on?
Anyone with an EQ, or a free version of Cool Edit can make this, monoural sounding, draw of the lot, into a real jewel...........  Behold!
If the good lord had created anything better, he would'd have kept it for himself!

vg rec, pg show vg recording. Bit of chatter, but luck of the draw with FOB's. Not sure what last reviewer was hearing as this is not monaural at all. Performance-wise, set 1 has some real promise, but set 2 is a bit labored, not bad, but puts a lot of pressure on the new tunes and just doesn't really take off.
- Excellent show altogether, particularly the encore!
